          <center><p>Feline Immunodeficiency Virus (FIV) is a virus that weakens a cat's immune system, making them more prone to infections. It's mainly spread through deep bite wounds, so outdoor and feral cats are at higher risk. Infected cats may not show symptoms for years but can develop issues like respiratory infections and dental problems over time.</p></center>  
